item.title: CVE-2019-6599|2024-09-16T20:27:53.623Z -- f5%20networks%2C%20inc. -- big-ip%20apm%3B%20enterprise%20manager
item.description: In BIG-IP 11.6.1-11.6.3.2 or 11.5.1-11.5.8, or Enterprise Manager 3.1.1, improper escaping of values in an undisclosed page of the configuration utility may result with an improper handling on the JSON response when it is injected by a malicious script via a remote cross-site scripting (XSS) attack.
